Cell.Text: [S] Turn back, traveler! Terror waits within this mist. | Many have braved the shadowed vale but vain is all courage against the peril that guards the way.
GS|In life I felled foes unnumbered, fearless in battle; but no blade can defend against the terror of this gloom-stricken valley.

G|When Ulfric Stormcloak, with savage Shout, sent me here, my sole regret was fair Elisif, left forlorn and weeping. | I faced him fearlessly - my fate inescapable, yet my honor is unstained - can Ulfric say the same?

G|Your heart was true, like the Harbingers of old. When I woke from cold death, my doom was lifted - there was Shor's Hall, my heart's desire. | But now I wander, weary and lost. Alduin hunts me as we once hunted our prey - a bitter payment for many bloody deeds.

G|The bitter war of the world beyond was all for naught. | We are all trapped in Alduin's web - for our allegiance he cares not, but devours us equally - doom unescapable. | Shor as well - he welcomes all heroes to his kingly hall, if we could but reach it.

G|Skyrim was betrayed, the blood of her sons spilled in doomed struggle against fate. | And so in death, too late, I learn the truth - fed by war, so waxed the powerof Alduin, World-Eater - wisdom now useless. | By gods' jest in this grim mist together snared, Stormcloak and Imperial, we wander hopeless, waiting for succor.
G|Dragonborn, even in death you dog my steps? | How come you here? The king of this realm will cast you out - cursed be your name by all sons of Skyrim, with scorn unceasing.
G|<<Shared>> Beware! The World-Eater waits within the mist!
G|Do you know the way? I'm weary and lost.
G|Turn back! Before he finds you!
G|<<Shared>> There is no escape. Courage is useless.

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: Near Giants' Gap, in the gloom before dawn, we marched, unsuspecting into the Imperials' trap. | Then we stood and fought, our shield-wall defending until by dawn's light the Legion's ranks wavered. | But I never knew if nights-end brought victory - a swift-flying arrow to Sovngarde carried me.

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulA1: Who are you?

Cell.Text: I do not know - but none have passed through. | Alduin, his hunger insatiable, hunts the lost souls snared within this shadowed valley. | Can you lead the way to where Shor's hall waits, beckoning us on to welcome long sought?

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulA2: What's this mist?

Cell.Text: [S] I saw it fair when first I trod this long-sought path. The pain and fear vanished, dreamlike, and a vision beckoned - | Shor's hall, shimmering across the clouded vale. But quenched was hope by the shrouding mist - my mind is darkened. | I've lost the way and wander blindly. | Hurry! Before Alduin your life devours bring word to Shor's hall of our hard fate!

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulB1: Yes, it's at the far end of the valley from here.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I'll try to hold to your hopeful purpose. Quickly, before this encompassing fog once more snares me in the World-Eater's net.

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulC1: Follow me. I'll lead you through this mist.

Cell.Text: G|<<Shared>> Beware! The World-Eater waits within the mist!

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulC2: Don't worry, I'm here to kill Alduin.

Cell.Text: [S] G|The World-Eater waits within the mist! Bring word to Shor's hall of our hard fate!

Node.Caption: MQ304A3: Invisible Walk Away

Cell.Text: Don't you know? What drew you here? Surely your dreams showed you the way? | The Hall of Valor, where heroes wait to follow Shor to the final battle.

Node.Caption: MQ304LostSoulB2: Shor's hall? What's that?

Cell.Text: G|Shor's favor has found you, Dragonborn. The Hall of Valor, heart's-ease, awaits.
[S] G|<<Shared>> Living or dead, by decree of Shor, none may pass this perilous bridge 'til I judge them worthy by the warrior's test.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: Ah! It's been too long since last I faced a doom-driven hero of the dragon blood.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroA1: By the right of birth. I am Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Living or dead, by decree of Shor, none may pass this perilous bridge 'til I judge them worthy by the warrior's test.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroB1: Can I enter the Hall of Valor?

Cell.Text: I welcome the chance to challenge the blade of Ysgramor's heir, honored shield-brother to Kodlak Whitemane, whom I've watched for in vain.
I welcome the chance to challenge the blade of Ysgramor's heir, honored shield-sister to Kodlak Whitemane, whom I've watched for in vain.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroA2: By right of glory. I lead the Companions of Jorrvaskr.

Cell.Text: Well met, mage of Skyrim. | The Nords may have forgotten their forefathers' respect for the Clever Craft, but your comrades throng this hall. | Here in Shor's house we honor it still.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroA3: By right of Cleverness. I am Master of the College of Winterhold.

Cell.Text: You trespass here, shadow-walker. Shor does not know you. | Perhaps before the end you will earn the right to pass this way. | Welcome I do not offer, but your errand I will not hinder, if my wrath you can withstand.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroA4: By right of blood. I Listen for the Night Mother.

Cell.Text: Do not mistake the night-shrouded thief's stealthily-taken spoils, stolen and unearned, for a warrior's plunder, won in honorable battle. | Your doom already binds you to your dark mistress, but your errand I will not hinder, if my wrath you can withstand.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroA5: By right of plunder. I am a Nightingale of Nocturnal.

Cell.Text: G|Alduin escaped us long ago. Today we take our well-tempered revenge.
G|For a hundred lifetimes my heart has burned for revenge on Alduin too long delayed.
G|<<Shared>> The endless wait gives way to battle! Alduin's doom, his death or ours!

Node.Caption: MQ304HeroFightAlduinTopic: I need your help to defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: I am Tsun, shield-thane to Shor. | The Whalebone Bridge he bade me guard and winnow all those souls whose heroic end sent them here, to Shor's lofty hall | where welcome, well-earned, awaits those I judge fit to join that fellowship of honor.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroWhoAreYou: Who are you?

Cell.Text: A fateful errand. No few have chafed to face the Worm since first he set his soul-snare here at Sovngarde's threshold. | But Shor restrained our wrathful onslaught - perhaps, deep-counselled, your doom he foresaw.

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroAlduin: I pursue Alduin, the World-Eater.

Cell.Text: No shade are you, as usually here passes, but living, you dare the land of the dead. | By what right do you request entry?

Node.Caption: MQ304TsunIntroHallofValor: I seek entrance to the Hall of Valor.

Cell.Text: Welcome, Dragonborn! Our door has stood empty since Alduin first set his soul-snare here.
G|The three await your word to loose their fury upon the perilous foe.
G|Do not fail Kodlak. He's earned his place here, and does not deserve to fall prey to Alduin's insatiable hunger.
G|My disciples still follow the difficult path - the Way of the Voice is neither wide, nor easy. | But if you stray from wisdom then to Sovngarde you will not return.

G|You freed Svaknir, a fool of a poet, but an honest enemy who has earned my respect. | Sadly, he's now lost in the soul-snaring mist - defeat Alduin, and his doom avert - I hope to greet him in this Hall as a friend.
G|Fate drives you, but you follow your own path. Choose wisely, lest you wander into evil.
GS|Far you've travelled, your trials long, to taste of Sovngarde's sweet delights.
G|Seek ye food or song unending? Fighting, drinking, fellowship and boasting? Find welcome here, and warm your soul.
G|Hail, Dragonborn. That honor is also mine - to our shared birthright you'll bring new glory!
G|Dragonborn! Have you come to cleanse Sovngarde at long last of Alduin's foul mist?
G|Why does Shor forbid us to face Alduin? I fear no worm, World-Eater though he be.
G|I long to fight that foul worm, but by Shor's command we curb our wrath.
G|No gloom can hold my heart for long in Shor's bless'd hall, where no shadows lie.
G|A cup, Dragonborn, to death and glory!
G|Take your ease, let troubles fade.
G|By Shor's command we curb our wrath, so we feast and sing, til the final doom.
G|Shor's power protects this hall; but beyond is fear, brought by Alduin.
G|Shor's high seat stands empty; his mien is too bright for mortal eyes.

Node.Caption: MQ304HallofValorBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|By Shor's command we sheathed our blades and ventured not the vale's dark mist. | But three await your word to loose their fury upon the perilous foe. | Gormlaith the fearless, glad-hearted in battle; Hakon the valiant, heavy-handed warrior; Felldir the Old, far-seeing and grim.

Node.Caption: MQ304YsgramorIntro1
